    <field name="scopecontent_teim">The series consists of legal documents and subject files from court cases brought by Brenda Berkman against the City of New York and the New York City Fire Department between 1977 and 1993, and from an unsuccessful appeal by the City of New York to Judge Charles Sifton's 1982 ruling that the City had discriminated against women through its physical exam. The series includes materials from the following cases: Brenda Berkman et al. v. City of New York et al. (Case No. 79, C 1813) Class Action Suit (also known as "Berkman v. City of New York"), 1977-1990; Brenda Berkman et al. v. City of New York et al. (Case no. 82-7654) Appeal, 1982 (also known as "Berkman v. City of New York, Appeal"); and Brenda Berkman v. New York City Fire Department, Carlos Rivera, and Selig Ginsberg (Case no. E-92-0575), 1991-1993 (also known as "Berkman v. NYCFD").</field>
